data.enText: a group of stars that forms a shape in the sky and has a name

data.chText: 一系列（相关的想法、事物）；一群（相关的人）
data.enText: a group of related ideas, things or people

means: 一系列(相关的想法、事物)

tr: an arrangement of parts or elements
example: the outcome depends on the configuration of influences at the time

tr: a configuration of stars as seen from the earth

value.def: A constellation is a group of stars which form a pattern and have a name.

example.ex: ...a planet orbiting a star in the constellation of Cepheus.
example.tran: 围绕仙王座中一颗恒星旋转的行星

value.def: A constellation of similar things is a group of them.

example.ex: Most patients have a constellation of diseases, with few clear-cut distinctions between them...
example.tran: 大多数患者的病症都很相似，鲜有明显的区别。

example.ex: The largest gallery contains at its centre a constellation of photographs called My Wishes.
example.tran: 最大的画廊在中心位置展出了一组名为《我的心愿》的摄影作品。

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + stell 星星 + ate 使… → 星星聚到一起 → 形成星座
inter 在…之间 + stell 星星 + ar …的 → 星际的
stell 星星 + ar → 星的
stelli 星星 + form 形状 → 星形的
stelli 星星 + fy 使… → 使成星状
